      "writtenOn": "2021-03-18T14:35:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is what I was saying. When people do this on other OSes, they expect immediate upload. This is often used when the process is in a healthy state and a developer just wants to capture some data. App relaunch may not happen for a long time after.\n\nThis interface, CRASHPAD_SIMULATE_CRASH, should maintain that property.\n\nThere should be a different CRASHPAD_SIMULATE_CRASH_AND_DEFER_PROCESSING that you can use from your hang monitor or any place that iOS specifically wants to defer.\n\nCRASHPAD_SIMULATE_CRASH should be CRASHPAD_SIMULATE_CRASH_AND_DEFER_PROCESSING + ProcessIntermediateDumps.",
